# Android Release Signing — GitHub Secrets
#
# To sign release APKs, generate a keystore and configure these secrets
# in the GitHub "release" environment:
#
# 1. Generate a keystore:
#    keytool -genkey -v -keystore release.keystore -alias tapauth \
#      -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000 \
#      -storepass <password> -keypass <password> \
#      -dname "CN=Tapauth"
#
# 2. Base64-encode it for the secret:
#    base64 release.keystore > release.keystore.b64
#
# 3. Add these secrets to the "release" environment:
#    ANDROID_KEYSTORE_B64       — content of release.keystore.b64
#    ANDROID_KEYSTORE_PASSWORD  — keystore password
#    ANDROID_KEY_ALIAS          — key alias (default: tapauth)
#    ANDROID_KEY_PASSWORD       — key password (defaults to store password)
#
# Without these secrets, the workflow produces an unsigned APK.
